biogHist.abstract: The John Mulligan Photograph Collection, ca. 1960-1976 is a collection of photographs taken by John Aloysius Mulligan between 1960 and 1976. The subjects are social, religious and cultural events in Australia. The acetate negatives have been discarded due to deteoriation but the National Library of Australia holds digital copies of all the images. The collection includes a series of photos of the Home of the Good Shepherd and images involving children of the Big Brother Movement, Royal Far West and St Edmund's School. There are also images of babies at the Royal Hospital for Women and a few photos of the Metropolitan Children's Court on Albion Street.
biogHist.p: Restricted access may apply to some photographs.
The photographs in the collection were provided to a range of publications and organisations.
